  "title": "Reservations Officer - M Hotel Singapore",
  "description": "<p><strong>Position Summary:</strong></p><p>Reservations Officer is responsible for handling and managing the whole reservations process and to assist Reservations Manager in maximising room sales revenue for the hotel by up-selling and promoting of various room facilities while maintaining a consistently high standard of customer service.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>To maintain high team focus by showing co-operation and support to colleagues in the pursuit of team goals.</p></li><li><p>To be motivated and committed, approaching all tasks with enthusiasm and seizing opportunities to learn new skills or knowledge to improve your personal performance.</p></li><li><p>To take personal responsibility and initiative to resolve issues always clearly communicating with both customers and colleagues.</p></li><li><p>To respond quickly and positively to changing requirements including the performance of any tasks requested.</p></li><li><p>Establishes and maintains good relations with corporate accounts, travel agencies, airlines and other booking sources.</p></li></ul><ul><li><p>Maintain a very good reputation for the Hotel and assist to increase the overall profitability of the Hotel.</p></li><li><p>Be understanding and supportive, encouraging and helpful to all.</p></li><li><p>Maintain the reservations integrity - ensuring all information in PMS are accurate.</p></li><li><p>Provides guests with the most accurate and up to date information at all times.</p></li><li><p>To ensure Revenue strategies implemented are followed through.</p></li><li><p>Ensuring that all reports are completed on time.</p></li></ul>",
